introduction: This video provides an overview of a virtual conference that will take place on February 15th and 22nd, featuring AI product owners, engineering tracks, and hands-on workshops. The conference will include keynotes from notable AI experts, such as Jason Louie, Shrea Shanar, and Dro. The event aims to bring together AI professionals to discuss topics related to product management, engineering, and AI product owner tracks. The conference will also feature a Q&A session with a judge, where attendees can ask questions about the policy and the response generated by the model. The video highlights the importance of context length and span evaluation in AI models and the role of benchmarks in the AI community.
